"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66215","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-10","<p>For all disabled former Remploy workers made redundant as a result of factory closures, the Government put in place the £8 million guaranteed People Help and Support Package (PHSP). The support package provides help to each affected disabled former employee for up to 18 months from the date they left Remploy.</p><p>The PHSP includes one-to-one support from a personal case worker to identify suitable help to find work including access to advice, and a personal budget. Personal budget awards can pay for items such as training, tools and equipment. After 18 months is complete, specialist support will continue to be available, usually from the same specialist employment advisor.</p><p>Former employees have also been referred to Community Support Fund projects where, in areas affected by factory closures, local organisations support former Remploy workers to move into employment and take part in social activities.</p><p>Latest figures show that 1,506 disabled former Remploy workers are choosing to work with our personal case workers to find another job and 774 are in work. 259 disabled former Remploy employees have been supported by the Access to Work scheme since they left the factories.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66215/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-10T14:03:31.9261835Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66215/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66215/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-07","Remploy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps his Department has taken to work with Remploy factory workers since the factory closure programme began; how many former Remploy factory employees are now in mainstream work; and how many former Remploy employees have been supported by the Access to Work scheme since the factory closure programme began.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","204148"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66216","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-10","<p /> <p /> <p>In July 2012 the Department consulted extensively on the future of the Independent Living Fund, including a large number of disability organisations. The consultation received approximately 2000 responses, 79 of these responses were from disability organisations.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66216/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-10T14:08:26.3218667Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66216/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66216/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-07","Independent Living Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what discussions he has had with learning disability charities on the closure of the Independent Living Fund.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham Jones","204156"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66217","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-10","<p /> <p /> <p>The potential implications of closing the Independent Living Fund and devolving the full funding to Local Authorities (LA) are set out clearly in the Equality Analysis published on 6 March 2014.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66217/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-10T11:08:16.2992108Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66217/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66217/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-07","Independent Living Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effect on learning disability outcomes of the closure of the Independent Living Fund.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham Jones","204155"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66218","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-10","<p>The information requested in respect of Jobseeker's Allowance (JSA) and Employment and Support Allowance (ESA) is shown in the table below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Number of individuals with an adverse benefit sanction overturned in Bethnal Green and Bow Parliamentary Constituency: January to December 2013</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Reconsideration 353</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Appeal 19</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total 363</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Source: DWP Information, Governance and Security Directorate: Sanctions and Disallowance Decisions Statistics Database.</p><p> </p><p>Notes:</p><p>1. Statistical disclosure control has been applied to protect against the identification of individual claimants.</p><p>2. The data provided is for the number of appeals and reconsiderations overturned in Bethnal Green and Bow Parliamentary Constituency for JSA and ESA only. The decision to apply a sanction can be overturned following reconsideration or appeal by the Sector Decision Maker.</p><p>3. The information shown in the table is published at:</p><p><a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/</a></p><p> </p><p>The information requested on Income Support Lone Parents is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66218/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-10T14:46:54.0473198Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66218/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66218/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-07","Social Security Benefits: Tower Hamlets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many benefit claimants from Bethnal Green and Bow constituency had benefit sanctions overturned in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Rushanara Ali","Bethnal Green and Bow","Rushanara Ali","204203"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66219","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-10","<p /> <p /> <p>The available information as requested is shown in the table below.</p><p> </p><p>Number of individuals with an adverse benefit sanction applied by geography:</p><p>January to December 2013.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>England</p></td><td><p>520,740</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>London</p></td><td><p>89,080</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Parliamentary Constituency:</p><p>Bethnal Green and Bow</p></td><td><p>2,250</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Source (JSA and ESA): DWP Information, Governance and Security Directorate: Sanctions and Disallowance Decisions Statistics Database.</p><p>Source (IS): Income Support Computer System</p><p> </p><p>Notes:</p><p>1. Figures have been rounded to the nearest 10.</p><p>2. The number of benefit sanctions applied is the number of claimants with a sanction or disallowance referral where the decision was found against them for those in receipt of Jobseeker's Allowance, Employment and Support Allowance and Income Support for Lone Parents.</p><p>3. New sanctions rules came into force for JSA and ESA from 22 October 2012 and 3 December 2012. The number of JSA sanctions applied for the new regime is the number of low, intermediate, and high level referrals where the decision was found against the claimant. Further information can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/jobseekers-allowance-overview-of-sanctions-rules" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/jobseekers-allowance-overview-of-sanctions-rules</a></p><p>4. Income Support Lone Parents receive a fixed sanction of 20% of the personal allowance rate of a single claimant (not aged less than 25) for each failure to attend/participate in a Work Focused Interview until 10 pence is left in payment. This sanction lasts until the individual attends and participates in a Work Focused Interview. In the case where there is more than one sanction in place the claimant need only attend/participate in one Work Focused Interview in order for all related sanctions to be removed from their benefit.</p><p>5. This information for JSA and ESA sanctions is published at: <a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/</a></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66219/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-10T15:03:41.9975222Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66219/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66219/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-07","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many benefit claimants from (a) England, (b) London and (c) Bethnal Green and Bow constituency were sanctioned in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Rushanara Ali","Bethnal Green and Bow","Rushanara Ali","204200"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66220","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-10","<p /> <p /> <p>I refer the Rt. Hon. Member to my previous answer to the hon. Member for Torbay, Mr Adrian Sanders, <em>Official Report</em>, 13 March 2014, column 318W. Our position has not changed.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66220/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-10T14:26:11.775479Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66220/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66220/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-07","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what representations he has received in support of maintaining the local welfare provision grant to local authorities; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","204263"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66221","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-21","<p>Holding reply issued 10th July 2014.</p><p>451,207 men and 174,733 women have claimed jobseekers allowance between 01 January and 31 March 2014 where they had ended a jobseekers claim in the previous 6 months.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66221/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-21T14:17:53.4463249Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66221/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66221/answer","Wirral West","Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66221/answer/previousversion/9524","Biography information for Esther McVey","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-07","Jobseeker's Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many claims for jobseeker's allowance made by (a) men and (b) women in the first quarter of 2014 were made within six months of a previous claim ending.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","204266"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66222","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-10","<p /> <p /> <p>Information on the number of individuals helped by the Access to Work scheme each year are only available back to 2007, and up to Q3 (31<sup>st</sup> December 2013). The requested information is already published from 2007 onwards, and can be found within table 1 on page 8 of the latest publication at the link below:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/303353/access-to-work-statistics-april-2014.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/303353/access-to-work-statistics-april-2014.pdf</a></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66222/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-10T14:38:47.2113035Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66222/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66222/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-07","Access to Work Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many disabled people entered the Access to Work scheme in each year since 2004.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","204256"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66223","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-10","<p /> <p /> <p>The information requested is not available.</p><p> </p><p>Estimates of the number of people in low income households are published in the National Statistics Households Below Average Income (HBAI) series. HBAI uses household income adjusted (or ‘equivalised') for household size and composition, to provide a proxy for standard of living. This information is captured using the Family Resources Survey.</p><p> </p><p>The latest figures for people reported to be in relative and absolute poverty by the HBAI series can be found in the latest HBAI publication, available at the link below:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/325416/households-below-average-income-1994-1995-2012-2013.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/325416/households-below-average-income-1994-1995-2012-2013.pdf</a> (ISBN 978-1-78425-188-8)</p><p> </p><p>Supporting data tables, which include figures for each region of the UK, are available at the link below:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/households-below-average-income-hbai-199495-to-201213" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/households-below-average-income-hbai-199495-to-201213</a></p><p> </p><p>Information atconstituency or local authority level is not available as the sample size of the Family Resources Survey is not sufficient to provide robust estimates. The lowest geography at which poverty estimates are reported is regional level.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66223/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-10T14:55:23.7877523Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66223/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66223/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-07","Poverty: Warrington","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in (a) Warrington Borough and (b) Warrington North constituency were in (i) relative and (ii) absolute poverty in 1997-98 and each year since.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","204253"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66224","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-14","<p /> <p /> <p>We still plan to complete the process of having invited all eligible disability living allowance claimants to claim personal independence payment (PIP) by late 2017. Therefore, our overall assessment of the impacts of the introduction of PIP hasn't changed. We are still on course to make savings against earlier forecasts of £2.8 billion by 2017/18.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66224/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-14T16:42:51.7365899Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66224/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66224/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-07","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 10 June 2014, Official Report, column 126W, on personal independence payment, and with reference to the National Audit Office report, Personal Independence Payment: early progress, how his Department plans to recoup the £140 million shortfall in benefit savings estimated in that report while delivering the PIP reassessment programme within its original timescales and budget.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","204224"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66225","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-10","<p /> <p /> <p>The Department's approach to the social cost-benefit analysis of employment programmes is outlined in DWP Working Paper No. 86 (available via <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/214384/WP86.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/214384/WP86.pdf</a>). The Department is currently considering the extent to which this methodology can be applied to Access to Work.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66225/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-10T14:33:55.3921802Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66225/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66225/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-07","Access to Work Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what methodology is used by his Department to assess the comparative costs and benefits of the Access to Work scheme.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","204252"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76528","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-10","<p> </p><p>The figures for 2013 show the lowest number of road deaths since records began.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government is working on a range of measures to continue to improve road safety including introducing a new drug driving offence, cycle proofing roads, and removing the “statutory option” to ensure more drink drivers are brought to justice.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76528/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-10T13:54:45.335553Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76528/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76528/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-07","Roads: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of recent trends in reported road casualties.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","904767"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76529","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-10","<p> </p><p>The figures for 2013 show the lowest number of road deaths since records began.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government is working on a range of measures to continue to improve road safety including introducing a new drug driving offence, cycle proofing roads, and removing the “statutory option” to ensure more drink drivers are brought to justice.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76529/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-10T13:24:27.8584235Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76529/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76529/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-07","Roads: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of recent trends in road safety statistics.","false","Biography information for Rehman Chishti","Gillingham and Rainham","Rehman Chishti","904765"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76530","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-10","<p> </p><p>On Monday of this week we published the Local Enterprise Partnership (LEP) Growth Deals, including both Deals which cover Hampshire; Solent LEP and EM3 LEP.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Working with the Solent LEP, Government has agreed to fund 2 schemes to relieve congestion on the Gosport peninsula.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Gosport Road and A27 improvement scheme and The Peel Common Roundabout Improvement scheme, a pinch point on the local road network near the Enterprise Zone, Daedalus.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>While Stubbington Bypass and the Newgate Lane South schemes were not allocated funding in the deal directly, there is a commitment for the Government and the LEP to negotiate in 2014 a further phase of co investment to deliver strategic infrastructure to support the development of network capacity to and from the Gospport peninsula – including Stubbington Bypass.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Working with the EM3 LEP, Government has agreed to fund 3 schemes to relieve congestion around Basingstoke; Basingstoke Northern Corridor to Growth A33, Basingstoke North Eastern Corridor A340 partial dualling and the Basingstoke South Western Corridor scheme. All of these schemes will reduce current congestion levels and help mitigate future congestion from new housing and business sites.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Whitehill/Bordon Relief road will remove the severance caused by the A325 and improve traffic flows through the towns to reduce congestion.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>EM3 have also been allocated £20.7m, with £4.3m in the first year to for a transport fund which will comp[rise of sustainable transport schemes to alleviate congestion in the identified growth and step up towns within the LEP area</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76530/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-10T13:28:57.3101747Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76530/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76530/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-07","Road Traffic Control: Hampshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans he has to relieve congestion on roads in Hampshire.","false","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","904753"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76531","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-10","<p> </p><p>The Government's goal for high speed rail is for a truly national network that will bring the UK and its cities closer together. We are clear that the benefits of high speed rail should extend as widely as possible, and we will continue to explore options for future links to achieve this.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76531/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-10T13:51:02.7634832Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76531/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76531/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-07","Railways: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans the Government has for further high-speed rail developments.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","904766"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76532","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-10","<p> </p><p>After a successful initial six-week period, the pilot of a new enforcement process has been extended to August. There has been very positive feedback from the police forces involved. The Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency is continuing to work with the police to develop a more effective approach for dealing with foreign registered vehicles that have overstayed.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76532/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-10T13:39:32.3922959Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76532/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76532/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-07","Motor Vehicles: Registration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent progress his Department has made on the pilot of a new enforcement process for foreign-registered vehicles that have overstayed.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","904754"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76908","Leader of the House","false","2014-07-10","<p> </p><p>The Ministerial Code is clear; when Parliament is in session the most important announcements of Government policy should be made in the first instance to Parliament.</p><p> </p><p>I regularly remind my colleagues of this.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Cambridgeshire","Mr Andrew Lansley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76908/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-10T14:03:37.1665928Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76908/answer","Biography information for Lord Lansley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76908/answer",,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2014-07-07","Ministers: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, what recent guidance he has given to his ministerial colleagues on making statements to the House before they are made to the media.","false","Biography information for Pat Glass","North West Durham","Pat Glass","904796"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76909","Leader of the House","false","2014-07-10","<p>I have regular discussions with ministerial colleagues about legislation before the House, including Private Members' Bills.</p>","South Cambridgeshire","Mr Andrew Lansley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76909/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-10T14:05:12.6970408Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76909/answer","Biography information for Lord Lansley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76909/answer",,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2014-07-07","Private Members' Bills","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, what recent discussions he has had with his ministerial colleagues about Private Members' Bills.","false","Biography information for Mr William Bain","Glasgow North East","Mr William Bain","904789"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76924","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-10","<p> </p><p>It is for the south west local authorities and the local enterprise partnership to continue to stress the importance of additional rail route to connect Plymouth to London and the Midlands.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>However, I would like to emphasise that a long term resilient rail route to Plymouth and far South West is a priority for this Government. Network Rail is reviewing measures of improvement in a number of key locations on the Western Route.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76924/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-10T13:59:31.9653425Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76924/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76924/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-07","Railways: Plymouth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what progress his Department has made on a second railway line to connect Plymouth with London and the Midlands.","false","Biography information for Oliver Colvile","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Oliver Colvile","904748"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76941","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-10","<p> </p><p>Road investment is central to our long term economic plan. We are spending more than £24 billion on strategic roads between 2010 and 2021. A further £7.4 billion will be spent on local roads in the next Parliament, together with £1.5bn funding from the Local Growth Fund announced on Monday. This will bring forward much needed schemes like the Stafford Western Access route, which are designed to relieve congestion and open up growth across the country.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76941/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-10T14:08:23.3054265Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76941/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76941/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-07","Road Traffic Control","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans he has to relieve congestion on roads.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Lefroy","Stafford","Jeremy Lefroy","904749"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76942","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-10","<p> </p><p>Since 2007 the Government has invested around £500 million specifically in improvements to rail freight infrastructure, and we have committed a further £200 million over the next five years. The amount of freight moved on our railways has almost doubled since 1994.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The only railway infrastructure in Britain that can accommodate lorry trailers on trains is HS1 between the Channel Tunnel and Barking, which can carry the standard international 4 metre semi-trailer. It represents 0.75% per cent of Britain's rail route mileage.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Around 80% of the UK domestic semi-trailer fleet has a height of 4.25 metres or greater. These cannot be accommodated on trains in Britain.</p><p> </p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76942/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-10T14:06:10.4659877Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76942/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76942/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-07","Railways: Freight","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what proportion of Britain's rail track mileage is capable of accommodating full-sized lorry trailers on trains.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","904750"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76965","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-10","<p> </p><p /> <p>The Aviation Policy Framework that the Government published last year recognises the very important role airports across the UK play in providing domestic and international connections and their vital contribution to the growth of regional economies. Only last month the Airport Operators Association published thirteen case studies illustrating this – with Newcastle taking centre stage.</p><p />","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76965/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-10T12:01:07.904086Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76965/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76965/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-07","Airports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the economic and social contribution of airports to (a) the Exchequer and (b) the local communities they serve; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame M. Morris","904764"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65850","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-07-09","<p> </p><p>Information on Apprenticeship starts by gender and age is published in a supplementary table, entitled <em>Breakdown by age, gender and level: starts 2002/03 to 2012/13</em>, to a Statistical First Release (SFR). The age breakdowns provided are under 19, 19-24 and 25+.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-apprenticeships--2" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-apprenticeships--2</a></p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/317564/apprenticeship-starts-by-age-gender-level.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/317564/apprenticeship-starts-by-age-gender-level.xls</a></p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65850/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-09T15:20:02.2817093Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65850/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65850/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-07-04","Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many apprenticeships have been taken up by (a) men and (b) women (i) aged up to 21 years, (ii) aged 22 to 24 years and (iii) aged 25 years and above in the last year.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","204107"
