"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65710","Department of Health","false","2014-07-09","<p>The Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency keeps the safety of all medicines, including emergency hormonal contraception, under continuous review.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65710/answer",,,,,"204000","2014-07-09T13:48:29.4263878Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65710/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65710/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-03","Contraceptives","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will make an assessment of the effects of the use of emergency hormonal contraception on the rate of abortion in women aged under 25; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","204001"
