"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65830","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>The Government of St Lucia has requested UK Police assistance with the investigation into the death of Oliver Gobat. In order to consider this request the British Government will require assurances that any person convicted of the alleged crime will not be sentenced to death and we are discussing this with the St Lucians. The Government opposes the use of the death penalty in all circumstances.</p>",,"Baroness Warsi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65830/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-14T10:41:51.2768509Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65830/answer","Biography information for Baroness Warsi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65830/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-03","St Lucia","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assistance is being given to the St Lucia police to find the murderer of Oliver Gobat, a British citizen; and if none, why.","false","Biography information for Lord Ashcroft",,"Lord Ashcroft","HL822"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65831","Home Office","false","2014-07-09","<p> </p><p> </p><p>Both the investigation and the misconduct proceedings are complete.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Taylor of Holbeach","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65831/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-09T12:46:05.7323861Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65831/answer","Biography information for Lord Taylor of Holbeach","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65831/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-03","Andrew Mitchell","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government when the Metropolitan Police Service expect to complete their investigation into the incident at the Downing Street gates on 19 September 2012 involving the Rt Hon Andrew Mitchell and a police officer; and whether the misconduct proceedings in relation to the incident have been completed.","false","Biography information for Lord Marlesford",,"Lord Marlesford","HL823"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65832","Home Office","false","2014-07-10","<p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The review of powers of entry has been carried out across Government. Departments are now completing their final reports which will then be laid <br>before Parliament.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Taylor of Holbeach","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65832/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-10T14:37:48.3905239Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65832/answer","Biography information for Lord Taylor of Holbeach","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65832/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-03","Powers of Entry","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Taylor of Holbeach on 29 January 2013 (WA 321), whether they have provided the final report to Parliament which was due by May 2014 setting out the findings of the full review of powers of entry required by the Protection of Freedom Act 2012.","false","Biography information for Lord Marlesford",,"Lord Marlesford","HL824"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65833","Home Office","false","2014-07-15","<p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Home Office is currently unable to confirm the total cumulative cost to public funds to date of the e-borders system, but we will be able to do this once the binding arbitration following the termination of the contract with Raytheon Systems Limited is complete.<br><br>The work of e-borders has been absorbed into the Border Systems Programme. By the end of this Parliament, Border Systems will:<br><br>• Develop replacement primary border security systems <br>• Deliver exit checks<br>• Improve resilience of all current business critical systems<br>• Increase Advance Passenger Information coverage<br>• Complete implementation of second generation e-Gates</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Taylor of Holbeach","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65833/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-15T13:42:53.8796264Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65833/answer","Biography information for Lord Taylor of Holbeach","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65833/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-03","Borders: Personal Records","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what has been the total cumulative cost to public funds to date of the introduction of the e-borders system in the United Kingdom; and when they expect the system to be fully operational.","false","Biography information for Lord Marlesford",,"Lord Marlesford","HL825"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65834","Home Office","false","2014-07-15","<p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government is committed to reintroducing exit checks. By April 2015, comprehensive exit checks will apply on scheduled, commercial air, sea and rail routes.<br><br>We are working collaboratively with carriers and port operators to identify the least burdensome way of delivering exit checks – we aim to use existing arrangements, including Advance Passenger Information, where possible, supplemented with embarkation checks at ports where necessary.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Taylor of Holbeach","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65834/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-15T13:30:22.1299Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65834/answer","Biography information for Lord Taylor of Holbeach","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65834/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-03","Passports","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether they plan to introduce routine electronic scanning of passports of passengers departing the United Kingdom; and when they expect to have this system completed.","false","Biography information for Lord Marlesford",,"Lord Marlesford","HL826"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65835","HM Treasury","false","2014-07-14","<p>The additional tax revenue HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) expects to collect through the use of this policy is represented in Table 2.1 of the Budget 2014 document.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As set out in paragraph 2.12 of the Direct Recovery of Debts consultation document, HMRC estimates that this measure will apply to around 17,000 debtors a year, who have an average of £5,800 in tax and tax credit debts and around £20,000 in their bank and building society accounts.</p>",,"Lord Deighton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65835/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-14T16:13:21.8608155Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65835/answer","Biography information for Lord Deighton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65835/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-03","Unpaid Taxes","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how much money is owed to HM Revenue and Customs by those whom they have contacted repeatedly to pay what they owe, as described in paragraph 2.4 of the HM Revenue and Customs report Direct Recovery of Debts published on 6 May 2014.","false","Biography information for Lord Howard of Rising",,"Lord Howard of Rising","HL827"
