"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65373","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-09","<p /> <p /> <p>Decisions around the future of DWP commissioned residential training college provision is still subject to internal departmental governance. We expect to be in a position to clarify this shortly.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65373/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-09T16:29:42.5800024Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65373/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65373/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-02","Employment Schemes: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when the proposed funding model for residential training colleges will be announced.","false","Biography information for Jesse Norman","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","203587"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65374","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-07","<p /> <p /> <p>HSE has concluded its sampling exercise with online sellers. A number of the different types of gas mask available were analysed and most found to contain asbestos. The placing on the market, supply and transport of almost all items containing asbestos, including gas masks, is prohibited by the EU Regulation on Registration, Evaluation, Authorisation and Restriction of Chemicals (EU1907/2006) (REACH).</p><p> </p><p>HSE and Trading Standards are working with the platform, which hosted the purchases of the gas masks involved in the study, on a policy to prohibit the sale of items that fall under REACH. <br> <br></p><p>HSE will continue work on a case by case basis with Local Authority Trading Standards, who are responsible for enforcement relating to sale to consumers, to take robust action against those who break the law on asbestos and unnecessarily put themselves and others at risk.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65374/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-07T16:45:52.3310624Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65374/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65374/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-02","Gas Masks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to the Answer of 25 November 2013, Official Report, column 126W, on gas masks, what progress he has made on preventing the continued on-line sale of Second World War gas masks containing asbestos.","false","Biography information for Annette Brooke","Mid Dorset and North Poole","Annette Brooke","203585"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65375","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-07","<p /> <p /> <p>The Health and Safety Executive continues to be a member of the Asbestos in Schools Steering Group which aim to promote the effective management of asbestos in both local authority and non-local authority controlled schools. The steering group has representatives from the joint Union Asbestos Committee, education trade unions, local authorities and independent schools.</p><p> </p><p>In June 2014, HSE published the results of its latest inspection survey into the management of asbestos in schools covering those outside local authority control. This survey showed improved levels of awareness and a decrease in the level of enforcement action required in comparison with a survey of the same sector in 2010/11. HSE also completed a similar inspection exercise in 2010 on local authority controlled schools.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65375/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-07T16:49:26.458746Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65375/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65375/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-02","Schools: Asbestos","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps he is taking to monitor the standards of asbestos management in schools (a) under and (b) outside of local authority control.","false","Biography information for Annette Brooke","Mid Dorset and North Poole","Annette Brooke","203583"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65376","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-07","<p> </p><p> </p><p>We announced our plans for the implementation of universal credit on 5 December, and these were set out in a written ministerial statement. The WMS can be found here:</p><p><a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201314/cmhansrd/cm131205/wmstext/131205m0001.htm#13120551000006" target="_blank">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201314/cmhansrd/cm131205/wmstext/131205m0001.htm#13120551000006</a></p><p> </p><p>Official statistics on universal credit were most recently published on 11 June and can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/universal-credit-statistics-apr-2013-to-31-march-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/universal-credit-statistics-apr-2013-to-31-march-2014</a></p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65376/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-07T15:06:22.9505399Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65376/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65376/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-02","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when the universal credit system will accept claims from those who are self-employed.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","203552"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65377","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-07","<p> </p><p> </p><p>The table below represents the number of claimants in receipt of Widowed Parent's Allowance who received an overpayment and DWP recorded a prosecution outcome.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="3"><p>Claimants in receipt of Widowed Parents Allowance</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Fiscal Year</p></td><td><p>Number of claimants who received an overpayment</p></td><td><p>Number of cases with a Prosecution Outcome</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009 – 2010</p></td><td><p>1.42K</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010 – 2011</p></td><td><p>1.48K</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011 – 2012</p></td><td><p>2.01K</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012 – 2013</p></td><td><p>2.59K</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013 – 2014</p></td><td><p>2.61K</p></td><td><p>6</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Wirral West","Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65377/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-07T15:54:16.8016596Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65377/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65377/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-02","Widowed Parent's Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many claimants (a) received an overpayment of widowed parent's allowance and (b) were prosecuted for benefit fraud in respect of that allowance in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","203553"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65378","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-09","<p /> <p /> <p>No such assessment is planned. There are safeguards in place in Universal Credit to ensure that we have the ability to split payments between partners in cases of domestic violence, allowing each claimant to receive a separate payment.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65378/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-09T14:37:58.309144Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65378/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65378/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-02","Universal Credit: Domestic Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will make an assessment of the risk of a link between the introduction of universal credit and levels of domestic violence.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","203595"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65379","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-07","<p /> <p /> <p /> <p>The Department is collecting information to understand how the introduction of mandatory reconsideration (MR) is operating.</p><p> </p><p>However, this data is not sufficiently robust and reliable to make available at this time.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65379/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-07T14:22:31.1328007Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65379/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65379/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-02","Work Capability Assessment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many decisions based on work capability assessments were overturned during the completion of the mandatory reconsideration period in (a) 2013-14 and (b) 2012-13.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","203624"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65380","Attorney General","false","2014-07-09","<p>The incorrect reclamation of VAT by the Serious Fraud Office (SFO) is an historical event which the Director of the SFO has taken steps to deal with. I am satisfied that it has no implications for the policies of the SFO.</p><p> </p>","North East Hertfordshire","Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65380/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-09T11:50:11.9679259Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65380/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65380/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2014-07-02","Serious Fraud Office","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what assessment he has made of the implications for his policies of the Serious Fraud Office's incorrect reclamation of VAT on fees it paid to barristers and other contractors; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","203779"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65381","Attorney General","false","2014-07-08","<p>The Crown Prosecution Service issued Legal Guidance on the new offence of Forced Marriage in June 2014. The Legal Guidance applies nationally and all prosecutors in the CPS, including those based in Northamptonshire, will refer to it when reviewing forced marriage cases. The CPS is also developing a new e-learning module on forced marriage for all prosecutors and expects to launch the module in July 2014, in addition to developing a joint training package with the police which will be delivered across all of the 13 CPS Areas this year.</p><p> </p>","North East Hertfordshire","Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65381/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-08T14:25:13.1853146Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65381/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65381/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2014-07-02","Forced Marriage: Prosecutions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what steps the Crown Prosecution Service is taking to prosecute successfully the offence of forced marriage in (a) Northamptonshire and (b) England.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Hollobone","Kettering","Mr Philip Hollobone","203838"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65382","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-07-09","<p>Higher education institutions are independent, autonomous bodies. As such, they are responsible for their own procurement policies and the transparency of their processes. Universities are able to draw upon the Higher Education Procurement Academy, a sector-led initiative to improve expertise and capacity in UK university procurement.</p>","Havant","Mr David Willetts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65382/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-09T16:04:32.740524Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65382/answer","Biography information for Lord Willetts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65382/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-07-02","Higher Education: Libraries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what recent steps he has taken to improve transparency in the procurement processes of university libraries.","false","Biography information for Ann McKechin","Glasgow North","Ann McKechin","203635"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65383","HM Treasury","false","2014-07-09","<p>The Government is committed to seeking ways to bring down the costs of car insurance for young drivers. Ministers recently held a roundtable for the insurance industry, at which it was agreed that the Government would commission new research into how telematics can change the behaviour and attitudes of learner drivers.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government is also in the process of undertaking some focus groups with parents, young people and employers to get a better understanding of the issues from their perspective. We will publish the findings of the research and focus groups in due course.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65383/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-09T15:14:14.1241755Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65383/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65383/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-02","Motor Vehicles: Insurance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he plans to bring forward proposals to help the insurance industry to reduce the cost of car insurance for newly qualified drivers.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","203643"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65384","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-07-07","<p> </p><p>We have and continue to actively engage with a wide range of stakeholders following the laying of a Written Ministerial Statement on Disabled Students' Allowances on 7 April. A list of those who have submitted information or evidence for the Equality Analysis and Disabled Students' Allowances Guidance for 2015-16 will be published as part of this document.</p><p> </p>","Havant","Mr David Willetts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65384/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-07T14:40:18.0807008Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65384/answer","Biography information for Lord Willetts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65384/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-07-02","Disabled Students' Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Answer of 18 June 2014, Official Report, column 649W, on disabled students' allowances, if he will publish a list of all stakeholders being consulted on the Equality Analysis and Disabled Students' Allowances Guidance for 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","203667"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65385","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-07-07","<p> </p><p>Information on students awarded and paid Disabled Students' Allowance is published annually by Student Loans Company (SLC) in the Statistical First Release ‘<em>Student Support for Higher Education England</em>'. The latest statistics are available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.slc.co.uk/media/694170/slcsfr052013.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.slc.co.uk/media/694170/slcsfr052013.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>A further breakdown for the London Borough of Lewisham and Lewisham East constituency has been provided in the table for the academic year 2012/13. The effective date is that of the November 2013 Awards Statistical First Release. The figures are therefore provisional and do not include students who were awarded DSA after November 2013.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Equivalent figures for the academic year 2013/14 will be available from November 2014.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>Students in receipt of Disabled Students Allowance<sup>(</sup></strong><strong><sup>1,2)</sup></strong><strong> from the London Borough of Lewisham<sup>(</sup></strong><strong><sup>3)</sup></strong><strong> and Lewisham East constituency<sup>(</sup></strong><strong><sup>3)</sup></strong></p><p> </p><p>Academic Year 2012/13 (provisional)</p><p> </p><p>Effective date: 13/11/2013<sup>(4)</sup></p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td colspan="4"><p>Application Type</p></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td><p>Full-Time Application</p></td><td><p>Part-Time Application</p></td><td><p>Post Graduate DSA</p></td><td><p>Total</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(Area)</p></td><td><p>No of Applicants Paid</p></td><td><p>No of Applicants Paid</p></td><td><p>No of Applicants Paid</p></td><td><p>No of Applicants Paid</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>London Borough of Lewisham</p></td><td><p>450</p></td><td><p>40</p></td><td><p>60</p></td><td><p>550</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Lewisham East Constituency</p></td><td><p>150</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>170</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Notes:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>1. Disabled Student Allowance (DSA) may be paid to the Student or to a Supplier on the student's behalf.</p><p> </p><p>2. DSA Payments may be made at any point during the Academic Year or after the end of the Academic Year.</p><p> </p><p>3. Figures are derived from the Post Code of the applicant's home address.</p><p> </p><p>4. The effective date is that of the November 2013 Awards Statistical First Release. The figures are therefore provisional and do not include students who were awarded DSA after November 2013.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Numbers are rounded to the nearest 10. Totals may not add to the sum of the components due to rounding.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Havant","Mr David Willetts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65385/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-07T13:12:24.6035319Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65385/answer","Biography information for Lord Willetts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65385/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-07-02","Disabled Students' Allowances: Lewisham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many people in (a) the London Borough of Lewisham and (b) Lewisham East constituency are in receipt of disabled student's allowance.","false","Biography information for Heidi Alexander","Lewisham East","Heidi Alexander","203720"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65386","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-07-07","<p> </p><p>Information on students awarded and paid Disabled Students' Allowance is published annually by Student Loans Company (SLC) in the Statistical First Release ‘<em>Student Support for Higher Education England</em>'. The latest statistics are available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.slc.co.uk/media/694170/slcsfr052013.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.slc.co.uk/media/694170/slcsfr052013.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>A further breakdown for the requested constituencies, local authorities and North East region has been provided in the table for academic years 2011/12 and 2012/13.</p><p> </p><p>The effective date is that used for the November 2013 Awards Statistical First Release. Hence, the figures for 2012/13 are classified as provisional and do not include students who were awarded DSA after November 2013.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Equivalent figures for the academic year 2013/14 will be available from November 2014.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong>Students in receipt of Disabled Students Allowance<sup>(1,2)</sup> in the North East region<sup>(3)</sup></strong></p><p> </p><p>Academic Year</p><p> </p><p>Effective date: 13/11/2013<sup>(4)</sup></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td colspan="8"><p><strong>Application Type</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td colspan="4"><p><strong>2011/12</strong></p></td><td colspan="4"><p><strong>2012/13<sup>(4)</sup></strong></p></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>Full-Time Application</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Part-Time Application</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Post Graduate DSA</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Full-Time Application</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Part-Time Application</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Post Graduate DSA</strong></p></td><t