"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65399","Cabinet Office","false","2014-07-09","<p>Cabinet Office provides security guidance to all departments</p><p>As was the case under successive administrations, we do not comment on the specifics of that advice.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65399/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-09T14:17:43.1445336Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65399/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65399/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-07-02","Security: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what guidance his Department provides to officials in the Northern Ireland Executive on personal security.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","203620"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65400","HM Treasury","false","2014-07-09","<p>Call handling supports compliance at the first point of contact by helping customers to get it right first time.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC has committed to delivering £24.5bn of compliance yield in 2014/15 – that commitment remains unchanged.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65400/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-09T16:52:38.0376789Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65400/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65400/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-02","Revenue and Customs","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the cost of flexible resourcing within HM Revenue and Customs in terms of lost yield from staff being moved away from their normal duties to assist with call handling during the tax credit peak.","false","Biography information for Katy Clark","North Ayrshire and Arran","Katy Clark","203798"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65401","HM Treasury","false","2014-07-09","<p>'Building our Future' is HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC's) vision for how it will serve its customers in the future, which it is currently presenting and discussing with its entire workforce. HMRC wants its employees to influence how the department is transforming to be a more effective, efficient and customer-focused organisation. The events started in May and will run until August 2014 and aim to bring together employees from different teams from across the department.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The final costs will be published on-line as part of the Government's commitment to transparency</p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65401/answer",,,,,,"2014-07-09T16:55:35.6880856Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65401/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65401/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-02","Revenue and Customs","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the cost to the public purse was of the Building Our Future workshops held for all HM Revenue and Customs staff.","false","Biography information for Katy Clark","North Ayrshire and Arran","Katy Clark","203797"
